Q.   Was there a certain time you thought might have been the lowest point throughout that process?
JAMES WHITE:   There was never a low point.   I play basketball for a living, even if I'm overseas and different places, you know, I play basketball for a living; I can't complain at all.   I get to do what I love to do every day. 

Q.   To come out to the All‑Star Weekend in Houston and showcase your skills, what is that like.   How would you characterize all that you've been through?
JAMES WHITE:   It's just my motto, continue to grind. 

Q.   Speaking of what you can do virally, people have seen the dunk, they love what they see, what should they expect this weekend?
JAMES WHITE:   Just the same.   The same excitement. 

Q.   A lot of celebrities out here for All‑Star Weekend, anybody you're excited to see? 
JAMES WHITE:   I got one of the biggest celebrities on my team. 







